flowRoot.flowPara: To improve the legibility of search results, each section gets a styled background on which to display text, opposed to displaying it over the desktop wallpaper which has varying impact on legibility.
The goal : to increase search result legibility and develop a pattern for showing results in more clearly delineated sections.
Bonus: show richer results and offer to do more with a query.
App results no longer have a special style and take on the appearance of the other sections as to appear more cohesive
Applications that provide results each draw their own results section and populate it with results. Clicking on results opens the application.
Results are richer and display the relevant application's icon or mimetype icons in the list.
When there is an excess of 3 results, an overflow item is shown in the section header alongside an expander.
Continue to offer to search the web in the shell but extend it with the ability to search various services online (ideally in the default browser). This would be configurable in Settings.
(Bring back the rounded search entry it was the best)
(On-the-fly dictionary definitions is more of a wishlist item)
Offer to perform the search query in other applications where it would be more appropriate or to be more helpful
In the case of overflow, expanding the search results section reveals more results (to some set maximum number of results) clicking again will hide the overflow results.
For an even deeper search (beyond the set maximum) offer to take the search to the relevant application.
